[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][csqa] sample 89/100 done id=3cb91a71a6567da870eedf37becc97ef prediction='To determine how going jogging generally affects one\'s self-esteem, let\'s consider each option:\n\n1. **Option A: Feel better**\n   - Jogging can improve physical health, which often leads to an overall feeling of well-being and happiness. This could indirectly contribute to improved self-esteem.\n\n2. **Option B: Feel pride**\n   - While jogging might make you feel proud of yourself for exercising regularly, it is more likely to be a result of personal achievement rather than a direct effect on self-esteem itself.\n\n3. **Option C: Sweating**\n   - Sweating during or after jogging is a physiological response that occurs as part of the body\'s cooling mechanism when exertion increases. It doesn\'t directly impact self-esteem but may influence mood.\n\n4. **Option D: Ocean**\n   - There is no clear evidence linking jogging specifically with being near or around oceans. This option seems unrelated to the effects of jogging on self-esteem.\n\n5. **Option E: Arthritis**\n   - Jogging has been shown to have positive effects on joint health, including reducing inflammation and improving mobility. These benefits could potentially lead to increased self-esteem.\n\nConsidering these points, the most plausible options affecting self-esteem through jogging are "feel better" (A) and "reduce arthritis symptoms' gold='A' correct=False
