[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 9/100 done id=mmlu_test_1169 prediction="To solve this problem, we need to analyze the given determinant equation and relate it back to properties of matrices.\n\nGiven:\n\\[ \\det(A - \\lambda I) = -\\lambda^3 + 3\\lambda^2 + \\lambda - 3 \\]\n\nThis polynomial can be factored as follows:\n\\[ -\\lambda^3 + 3\\lambda^2 + \\lambda - 3 = -( \\lambda - 1 ) ( \\lambda - 3 )^2 \\]\n\nFrom this factorization, we can identify the eigenvalues of \\( A \\):\n- One eigenvalue is \\( \\lambda = 1 \\)\n- Two eigenvalues are \\( \\lambda = 3 \\)\n\nNow let's evaluate each statement:\n\nI. **The trace of A is 3.**\n   - The trace of a matrix is the sum of its diagonal elements.\n   - Since one eigenvalue is 1 and two eigenvalues are 3, their sum is \\( 1 + 3 + 3 = 7 \\).\n   - Therefore, the trace of \\( A \\) is 7, not 3.\n\nII. **The determinant of A is −3.**\n   - The determinant of a matrix is the product of its eigenvalues" gold='D' correct=False
