[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 12/100 done id=mmlu_test_1424 prediction='To determine the uncertainty in the kinetic energy of the ball, we need to consider how uncertainties propagate through the formula for kinetic energy.\n\nThe kinetic energy \\( K \\) of an object is given by:\n\n\\[ K = \\frac{1}{2} m v^2 \\]\n\nwhere \\( m \\) is the mass of the ball and \\( v \\) is its velocity.\n\nGiven that the uncertainty in the measured speed \\( v \\) is 10%, we can express this as:\n\n\\[ \\Delta v = 0.1v \\]\n\nWe want to find the percentage uncertainty in the kinetic energy \\( K \\). To do this, we take the derivative of \\( K \\) with respect to \\( v \\):\n\n\\[ \\frac{\\partial K}{\\partial v} = mv \\]\n\nUsing the chain rule, the relative change in \\( K \\) due to a relative change in \\( v \\) is:\n\n\\[ \\frac{\\Delta K}{K} = \\left( \\frac{\\partial K}{\\partial v} \\right)_{m,v} \\cdot \\frac{\\Delta v}{v} \\]\n\nSubstituting the values:\n\n\\[ \\frac{\\Delta K}{K} = mv \\cdot \\frac{0.1v}{v' gold='D' correct=False
