[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 27/100 done id=mmlu_test_3432 prediction='To determine which demand of the Enlightenment philosophes the document supports, let\'s analyze each choice:\n\nA. "Deism should be adopted by all as the only logical religion."\n   - The text does not explicitly state that deism is the only logical religion. It mentions skepticism about established religions like Judaism, Christianity, and others, suggesting doubt rather than advocating for a single religion.\n\nB. "Religious toleration leads to the destruction of social unity."\n   - While the text discusses the abolition of compulsory systems of religion, it does not directly link religious toleration with the destruction of social unity. Instead, it emphasizes the importance of maintaining moral values despite changes in religious practices.\n\nC. "Skepticism is not a reliable way of examining information."\n   - The text criticizes certain religious beliefs (like those found in the Jewish, Roman, Greek, Turkish, and Protestant churches) and suggests skepticism towards them. However, it also encourages critical thinking through reason, indicating that skepticism can be a valuable tool.\n\nD. "Religious toleration should be given to all people of all religions."\n   - The text advocates for religious tolerance, stating that everyone should be free to hold their own opinions without fear of persecution. It also mentions the need for moral and humane principles' gold='D' correct=False
