[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 32/100 done id=mmlu_test_3733 prediction='To determine which option represents an implied power of the Congress, we need to understand what "implied powers" mean. Implied powers refer to those that cannot be explicitly stated but can be inferred from the Constitution\'s grants of authority.\n\n1. **Regulation of Interstate Commerce**: This is explicitly mentioned in Article I, Section 8, Clause 3 of the U.S. Constitution as one of the enumerated powers of Congress. Therefore, it is not an implied power.\n\n2. **Borrowing Money on the Credit of the United States**: This is also explicitly listed under the same clause (Article I, Section 8, Clause 4). Hence, it is not an implied power either.\n\n3. **Oversight of Executive Branch Agencies**: While there is no direct mention of oversight in the Constitution, the Supreme Court has ruled that Congress does have such oversight powers through its ability to appoint members of the executive branch and to hold them accountable. This interpretation is based on the principle of checks and balances and the separation of powers.\n\n4. **Declarations of War**: Although the Constitution gives Congress the power to declare war (Article I, Section 8, Clause 11), it does not specify how often or when this declaration should occur. The practice of' gold='C' correct=False
