[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 44/100 done id=mmlu_test_5514 prediction='To solve this problem, we need to understand what percentile means in terms of scores on a test. A percentile indicates the percentage of test-takers who scored below a certain score. \n\n1. **Identify Percentile Ranks**:\n   - Mary\'s score is at the 64th percentile, meaning 64% of the test-takers scored lower than her.\n   - Pam\'s score is at the 56th percentile, meaning 56% of the test-takers scored lower than her.\n\n2. **Compare Scores**:\n   - Since 64% scored lower than Mary but only 56% did so for Pam, it implies that Mary scored better than Pam.\n\n3. **Analyze Each Option**:\n   - **Option A**: "Mary scored eight more points than Pam."\n     - This is incorrect because we don\'t have information about individual scores; only their relative positions.\n   \n   - **Option B**: "Mary\'s score is 8% higher than Pam\'s."\n     - This is also incorrect without specific score values or additional context.\n   \n   - **Option C**: "Eight percent of those who took the test scored between Pam and Mary."\n     - This is correct because if 64% scored' gold='C' correct=False
