[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 76/100 done id=mmlu_test_10617 prediction='Step 1: Recall the Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM) formula:\n\\[ \\text{Required Return} = R_f + \\beta \\times (R_m - R_f) \\]\nwhere \\( R_f \\) is the risk-free rate, \\( \\beta \\) is the beta of the stock, and \\( R_m \\) is the expected return on the market.\n\nStep 2: Plug in the given values into the CAPM formula for both stocks:\n\nFor Plaid Pants, Inc.:\n\\[ \\text{Required Return}_{\\text{Plaid}} = 6\\% + 0.90 \\times (10\\% - 6\\%) \\]\n\nFor Acme Dynamite Company:\n\\[ \\text{Required Return}_{\\text{Acme}} = 6\\% + 1.80 \\times (10\\% - 6\\%) \\]\n\nStep 3: Calculate each required return:\n\\[ \\text{Required Return}_{\\text{Plaid}} = 6\\% + 0.90 \\times 4\\% = 6\\% + 3.6\\% = 9.6\\% \\]\n\\[ \\text{Required Return}_{\\text' gold='B' correct=False
