[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 90/100 done id=mmlu_test_12149 prediction="To determine whether the $100 per year excise tax on itinerant commercial figure drawers is constitutional, we need to analyze the nature of the tax and compare it with other relevant laws and principles.\n\nStep 1: Identify the type of tax involved.\nThe tax is a fee charged for the privilege of using the streets and sidewalks (excise tax) and a credit for taxes paid to the city for maintaining an artist's studio (credit).\n\nStep 2: Consider the purpose of the tax.\nThe primary purpose appears to be regulating the behavior of these artists who are traveling from one location to another to perform their work.\n\nStep 3: Compare with similar regulations.\nSimilar regulations exist in many states regarding the movement of individuals engaged in certain professions, such as solicitors or salesmen, who travel between different jurisdictions to provide their services.\n\nStep 4: Evaluate the impact on interstate commerce.\nWhile the tax affects interstate commerce indirectly through the activities of the artists, it does not directly regulate the flow of goods or services across state lines. Instead, it regulates the conduct of individuals within a single jurisdiction.\n\nStep 5: Assess the burden on interstate commerce.\nThe tax places a significant financial burden on the artists, potentially deterring them from performing their work if they cannot" gold='B' correct=False
