[zero_shot][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][mmlu] sample 92/100 done id=mmlu_test_12509 prediction='The correct answer is C. a special diet.\n\nStep 1: Understand the condition - Phenylketonuria (PKU) is an inherited metabolic disorder that affects individuals who lack the enzyme phenylalanine hydroxylase, which converts the amino acid phenylalanine into tyrosine.\n\nStep 2: Identify the cause - The primary cause of PKU is a genetic mutation that impairs the ability to metabolize phenylalanine properly.\n\nStep 3: Consider prevention options - Since PKU is caused by a genetic defect, it cannot be prevented through environmental factors like toxins or blood transfusions.\n\nStep 4: Evaluate dietary interventions - A special diet can help manage symptoms by reducing the intake of phenylalanine, which is harmful when accumulated in the body.\n\nStep 5: Eliminate incorrect options - Options A, B, and D do not address the underlying genetic basis of PKU and thus cannot prevent the condition.\n\nTherefore, the only option that addresses the root cause of PKU and provides a preventive measure is C. a special diet.' gold='A' correct=False
